<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-17T03:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-17T03:35:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1840: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-17T12:00:00+03:25">March 17,
                                    1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 17—9:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>73. The Prime Minister<note n="4" xml:id="d328fn4">Ali Soheily.</note>
                            was very much pleased when I communicated to him the contents of the
                            Department’s 66, March 13. He said <pb facs="0303" n="291" xml:id="pg_291"/> that he would like to be informed as soon as it
                            can be made public as he wishes to give it the widest possible publicity
                            here.</p>
                        <p>He volunteered the statement that he is keeping in mind the matter of the
                            expulsion of Japanese Legation.<note n="5" xml:id="d328fn5">For
                                correspondence on this subject, see <ref target="#pg_325">pp.
                                    325</ref> ff.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>